1
00:00:44,159 --> 00:00:44,799
Old Lu.

2
00:00:45,039 --> 00:00:46,079
What's the situation?

3
00:00:46,600 --> 00:00:48,719
Based on the Mengna Valley book's records,

4
00:00:48,960 --> 00:00:51,479
Chimi Jizhou was built inside a massive pit.

5
00:00:52,280 --> 00:00:54,479
The Kunlun Mountains went through complex tectonic shifts,

6
00:00:54,479 --> 00:00:56,880
with intense uplifts, folds, and fractures,

7
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,960
which formed the towering mountain range.

8
00:01:00,479 --> 00:01:01,719
So I'm wondering,

9
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:03,399
could it be that, with the tectonic movements,

10
00:01:03,399 --> 00:01:04,480
it's now buried deep underground?

11
00:01:04,480 --> 00:01:07,920
I think it might be an imaginary space.

12
00:01:10,319 --> 00:01:12,359
What on earth is that supposed to be?

13
00:01:12,359 --> 00:01:14,319
All morning I've heard you talk about

14
00:01:14,319 --> 00:01:15,000
this space and that space.

15
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:16,599
What does it actually mean?

16
00:01:18,599 --> 00:01:21,200
If the space we're in is real space,

17
00:01:21,359 --> 00:01:23,599
then an imaginary space might also exist.

18
00:01:23,760 --> 00:01:25,519
A single point in real space

19
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:27,079
could, in imaginary space,

20
00:01:27,159 --> 00:01:29,319
be an infinite 3D volume.

21
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:31,319
And an infinite 3D volume,

22
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:32,519
in imaginary space,

23
00:01:32,519 --> 00:01:33,719
could be just a single point.

24
00:01:35,560 --> 00:01:36,159
This...

25
00:01:37,120 --> 00:01:37,719
This, this, this...

26
00:01:37,959 --> 00:01:39,560
I don't get any of this.

27
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:40,519
What does it even mean?

28
00:01:40,680 --> 00:01:41,719
This imaginary space thing,

29
00:01:41,719 --> 00:01:43,560
I saw it before in Old Zhu's office,

30
00:01:43,959 --> 00:01:46,000
in a science magazine.

31
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:48,079
It's like how a convex lens works, right?

32
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:49,879
It's called...

33
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:52,719
What was it called again?

34
00:01:53,159 --> 00:01:54,439
Fourier transformer.

35
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,280
Right.

36
00:01:55,760 --> 00:01:56,920
That, uh, transformer thing.

37
00:01:57,359 --> 00:01:58,640
Why don't you explain it to everyone?

38
00:01:58,879 --> 00:02:01,400
It's basically how a convex lens works.

39
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,159
Say there's a convex lens here.

40
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:04,879
The Chimi Jizhou we're seeing

41
00:02:04,879 --> 00:02:06,239
is actually a virtual one,

42
00:02:06,920 --> 00:02:08,840
an image formed by a convex lens.

43
00:02:09,360 --> 00:02:11,039
If we find that convex lens,

44
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:14,400
we can pinpoint the real Chimi Jizhou.

45
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:17,840
Brother Chen, as far as the eye can see,

46
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:19,960
where on earth is there any convex lens?

47
00:02:30,520 --> 00:02:31,960
It's getting late now.

48
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:33,400
We should turn in early.

49
00:02:33,759 --> 00:02:35,560
We'll look for it first thing tomorrow.

50
00:02:38,159 --> 00:02:39,599
Guess that's all we can do.

51
00:02:39,879 --> 00:02:41,919
Then let's eat something first,

52
00:02:41,919 --> 00:02:43,719
turn in early, and head out at dawn.

53
00:02:44,840 --> 00:02:45,400
Let's go.

54
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:47,479
Anxiang.

55
00:03:13,039 --> 00:03:14,960
This wind-eroded lake is full of water,

56
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:15,960
high in the middle, low on the sides.

57
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:17,319
It's exactly a convex lens.

58
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:18,520
A convex lens?

59
00:03:19,360 --> 00:03:21,080
So, are you telling me

60
00:03:21,159 --> 00:03:23,240
Chimi Jizhou is at the lake bottom?

61
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,199
Then go find me another convex lens!

62
00:03:26,240 --> 00:03:27,400
Brother Chen,

63
00:03:27,439 --> 00:03:29,080
the lake bottom is solid, right?

64
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:30,560
So how can a convex lens

65
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:32,080
form anything?

66
00:03:32,080 --> 00:03:33,199
Project an image?

67
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:35,240
We just came up from the bottom yesterday.

68
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:37,080
Down there isn't solid ground.

69
00:03:37,120 --> 00:03:38,319
It's a transparent glacier.

70
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:39,479
Brother Chen,

71
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:42,400
if we go down to the lake bottom,

72
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:43,439
just think about it,

73
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:45,719
what if we run into another fish swarm,

74
00:03:45,719 --> 00:03:46,879
piranhas or something?

75
00:03:46,879 --> 00:03:49,280
Going back down to find Chimi Jizhou,

76
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:50,840
wouldn't that be a dead end?

77
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:52,560
Who said we're going into the lake?

78
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:54,520
If Chimi Jizhou really is down there,

79
00:03:54,599 --> 00:03:56,800
can you swim down and break the glacier?

80
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:58,159
Brother Chen,

81
00:03:58,479 --> 00:04:00,199
do you already have a route?

82
00:04:05,879 --> 00:04:06,439
Up the mountain.

83
00:04:06,439 --> 00:04:06,840
No way,

84
00:04:07,159 --> 00:04:08,680
climbing mountains again?

85
00:04:08,759 --> 00:04:09,560
Let's go.

86
00:04:14,479 --> 00:04:15,560
Such a beautiful lake,

87
00:04:15,560 --> 00:04:17,000
why don't we just swim across?

88
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:18,439
Another stupid idea.

89
00:04:18,439 --> 00:04:19,439
Swim if you want to.

90
00:04:19,519 --> 00:04:20,680
Walking is much safer.

91
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:22,040
What could be in there? Look,

92
00:04:22,519 --> 00:04:23,600
what could possibly be in it?

93
00:04:23,959 --> 00:04:24,759
Take a look.

94
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:29,759
Look, look!

95
00:04:29,959 --> 00:04:30,399
Look!

96
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:34,720
What...

97
00:04:36,519 --> 00:04:37,319
What is that thing?

98
00:04:37,319 --> 00:04:38,680
Calm on the surface,

99
00:04:39,079 --> 00:04:40,959
but undercurrents surging beneath!

100
00:04:46,120 --> 00:04:47,199
Quick, let's go, stay away from it!

101
00:04:47,199 --> 00:04:48,720
Wait, aren't you going down there?

102
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:49,399
No, no, no.

103
00:04:49,480 --> 00:04:50,600
Let's go swim at the reservoir instead.

104
00:04:51,399 --> 00:04:52,199
Go, go, go!

105
00:04:52,519 --> 00:04:53,519
Fatty,

106
00:04:53,759 --> 00:04:55,160
what on earth was that thing?

107
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:56,199
How would I know?

108
00:05:15,959 --> 00:05:16,360
Slow down!

109
00:05:19,759 --> 00:05:21,240
Anxiang, take it easy.

110
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:23,600
Godfather.

111
00:05:25,959 --> 00:05:27,360
What are you doing?

112
00:05:27,399 --> 00:05:29,279
This place is so dangerous!

113
00:05:30,279 --> 00:05:33,160
This cliff is bottomless!

114
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:35,000
If you had fallen just now,

115
00:05:35,319 --> 00:05:36,360
you'd be smashed to pieces.

116
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:40,240
If you want to back out, it's not too late.

117
00:05:41,040 --> 00:05:43,480
Did you pick this risky path on purpose,

118
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,560
to force me to give up?

119
00:05:46,199 --> 00:05:48,040
I'm not as scheming as you.

120
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:49,680
Relax.

121
00:05:50,759 --> 00:05:53,040
This is sedimentary rock. Very solid.

122
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:55,399
Hard to collapse, good for climbing.

123
00:05:55,959 --> 00:05:57,680
But the key question now is,

124
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,240
how can you guarantee

125
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:01,680
where to dig and where to tunnel?

126
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:03,519
If we can't find the underground cave,

127
00:06:03,639 --> 00:06:05,319
and we break through the lake bed,

128
00:06:05,319 --> 00:06:07,480
won't we all be walking to our deaths?

129
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:09,240
So that's what you're worried about.

130
00:06:12,279 --> 00:06:13,480
Have you ever dug a well?

131
00:06:14,839 --> 00:06:15,639
No.

132
00:06:15,839 --> 00:06:16,879
When digging a well,

133
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:18,639
the key is to find the aquiclude.

134
00:06:19,199 --> 00:06:22,199
Clay, shale, igneous rock, metamorphic rock.

135
00:06:22,319 --> 00:06:24,240
All easily form an aquiclude.

136
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:26,360
We just need to descend along this cliff.

137
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:28,360
Once we encounter such rocks,

138
00:06:28,439 --> 00:06:29,680
and find the aquiclude,

139
00:06:29,879 --> 00:06:31,199
we blast through from below,

140
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:33,279
and we'll definitely find Chimi Jizhou.

141
00:06:33,279 --> 00:06:33,959
No.

142
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:36,279
We don't know what's down there.

143
00:06:36,279 --> 00:06:37,360
Going down like this is too blind.

144
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:38,560
It's way too dangerous!

145
00:06:41,040 --> 00:06:41,720
Tell you what.

146
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,160
We go down first to scout.

147
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:44,199
Fatty.

148
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:46,199
Officer He and I will go first.

149
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:47,319
You and Old Lu follow after.

150
00:06:47,319 --> 00:06:47,959
Okay.

151
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:48,959
No, wait.

152
00:06:48,959 --> 00:06:50,399
I suggest, Brother Chen,

153
00:06:50,519 --> 00:06:51,920
that you go down alone.

154
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:53,639
We'll all wait up here.

155
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,360
Once you confirm it's safe down there,

156
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:57,120
then we'll follow you down.

157
00:06:57,399 --> 00:07:00,399
That'd be safer and more reliable.

158
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:10,439
Be careful.

159
00:07:10,439 --> 00:07:11,160
Got it.

160
00:07:14,519 --> 00:07:15,319
Take it slow!

161
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:18,399
Stay safe, Brother Chen!

162
00:07:22,839 --> 00:07:24,439
How did we end up running into

163
00:07:24,439 --> 00:07:26,160
such a bunch of lousy people?

164
00:07:26,639 --> 00:07:29,360
Why didn't he just fall and die earlier?

165
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,319
Here's what he's thinking.

166
00:07:32,639 --> 00:07:35,319
He and Old Chen are both dying men.

167
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:37,000
If he pushes Old Chen too far,

168
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,160
Old Chen might take him down with him.

169
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,040
Bite your tongue!

170
00:07:39,439 --> 00:07:40,839
You're the dying one!

171
00:07:40,839 --> 00:07:41,560
Right, right.

172
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,439
Found the aquiclude!

173
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,720
I'm setting up the explosives!

174
00:08:27,199 --> 00:08:28,319
Explosives?

175
00:08:29,319 --> 00:08:30,160
Be careful!

176
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,399
Watch out!

177
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:32,879
Take cover!

178
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:44,840
Old Chen!

179
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:45,600
Chen Youxi!

180
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:49,919
Are you okay?

181
00:08:50,399 --> 00:08:51,240
How is it?

182
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:52,919
I'm fine.

183
00:08:53,399 --> 00:08:54,519
The blast made a hole.

184
00:08:54,879 --> 00:08:55,960
I'm going to check it out.

185
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,240
All clear.

186
00:09:14,279 --> 00:09:15,320
You can come down now.

187
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:16,879
Okay.

188
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,200
Miss He,

189
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:23,399
I really envy your father.

190
00:09:24,279 --> 00:09:25,600
Don't tell me you wish

191
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:27,799
you had a daughter like me?

192
00:09:28,919 --> 00:09:31,759
Miss He, to be honest,

193
00:09:31,799 --> 00:09:32,919
as long as you're willing,

194
00:09:33,039 --> 00:09:34,759
you can be my goddaughter anytime.

195
00:09:35,039 --> 00:09:37,360
Just help me find Mengna Valley's secret,

196
00:09:37,399 --> 00:09:38,840
and you'll be my hero.

197
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:41,600
You can inherit all of my assets.

198
00:09:48,159 --> 00:09:49,679
We barely know each other.

199
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:52,279
How could I match Anxiang's devotion?

200
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,960
Of course you can't compare right now.

201
00:09:55,039 --> 00:09:56,720
But bonds grow over time.

202
00:09:56,759 --> 00:09:57,639
Besides,

203
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:00,519
compared to you, Anxiang's too young,

204
00:10:00,519 --> 00:10:01,720
too inexperienced.

205
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:04,799
Lacks experience and is far too timid.

206
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,080
I'm warning you,

207
00:10:07,679 --> 00:10:09,720
Anxiang trusts and is grateful to you.

208
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:11,240
You'd better drop that

209
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:13,039
use-and-discard routine of yours.

210
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:13,840
Otherwise,

211
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:16,080
you'll never find Mengna Valley's gates.

212
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:39,080
Fatty, stop swinging this rope, will you?

213
00:10:40,399 --> 00:10:41,879
Stop swinging the rope!

214
00:10:43,919 --> 00:10:45,000
Hurry, hurry, hurry!

215
00:10:45,440 --> 00:10:47,399
This is squeezing me to death!

216
00:11:00,679 --> 00:11:01,399
Old Lu!

217
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:05,960
Fatty, what's going on?

218
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:08,720
I can't hold on anymore!

219
00:11:24,080 --> 00:11:24,720
Old Lu!

220
00:11:25,279 --> 00:11:27,279
Find a spot and brace yourself first.

221
00:11:27,559 --> 00:11:29,240
I'll figure out a way to save you!

222
00:11:35,519 --> 00:11:36,879
Old Lu, hang on!

223
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:48,000
Damn Fatty, catch it!

224
00:12:08,679 --> 00:12:10,080
Okay, we're safe now.

225
00:12:10,679 --> 00:12:11,480
Safe...

226
00:12:13,679 --> 00:12:14,799
After you, Miss He.

227
00:12:17,759 --> 00:12:20,720
Mr. Bi, thanks for lending a rope

228
00:12:20,759 --> 00:12:22,120
at that critical moment.

229
00:12:22,240 --> 00:12:23,799
A true buddy, a real pal.

230
00:12:23,879 --> 00:12:24,679
Thanks.

231
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:32,799
Don't mention it.

232
00:12:56,919 --> 00:13:00,120
This might be the real Chimi Jizhou.

233
00:13:00,519 --> 00:13:01,759
These densely packed caves,

234
00:13:02,039 --> 00:13:03,600
like a honeycomb,

235
00:13:03,759 --> 00:13:04,519
must be where the Mengna Valley people

236
00:13:04,519 --> 00:13:05,840
once lived back then.

237
00:13:05,919 --> 00:13:07,440
According to the Book of Mengna Valley,

238
00:13:08,159 --> 00:13:09,279
the altar of Mengna Valley

239
00:13:09,279 --> 00:13:10,919
lies at the very bottom of Chimi Jizhou.

240
00:13:11,240 --> 00:13:13,639
It's an energy field of the serpent god.

241
00:13:14,559 --> 00:13:16,480
So in Mengna Valley's social hierarchy,

242
00:13:16,480 --> 00:13:18,360
the lower you go, the higher the rank.

243
00:13:18,799 --> 00:13:21,679
These caves connect and descend in layers.

244
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:25,080
If we just keep heading down the caves,

245
00:13:25,399 --> 00:13:27,159
we should be able to find the altar.

246
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:34,320
What's going on?

247
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:42,759
I'm guessing that explosive earlier

248
00:13:43,799 --> 00:13:45,080
went off way bigger than expected.

